messages.content: You are an AI assistant that helps people find information. You will receive a task and think step by step. Then provide your final outcome following the regular expression 'Answer: ([A-Za-z ]+,\s*)*[A-Za-z ]+'

Imagine a flower county with 16 flower fields. The rose field is connected to the sunflower field, tulip field, daisy field, and lily field. The sunflower field is connected to the rose field, tulip field, daisy field, and aster fields. The tulip field is connected to the rose field, sunflower field, daisy field and orchid field. The daisy field is also connected to the rose field, sunflower field, tulip field, and zinnia field. The orchid field is connected to the hydrangea field, lily field, daffodil field, and tulip field. The hydrangea field is connected to the orchid field, lily field, peony field, and marigold field. The lily field is connected to rose field, peony field, hydrangea field, and orchid field. The peony field is also connected to the orchid field, hydrangea field, lily field, and chrysanthemum field. The daffodil field is connected to the chrysanthemum field, carnation field, marigold field, and lavender field. The chrysanthemum field is connected to the daffodil field, carnation field, peony field, and marigold field. The carnation field is connected to the poppy field, daffodil field, marigold field, and chrysanthemum field. The marigold field is also connected to the daffodil field, chrysanthemum field, carnation field, and hydrangea field. The poppy field is connected to the zinnia field, lavender field, aster field, and carnation field. The zinnia field is connected to the daisy field, poppy field, lavender field, and aster field. The lavender field is connected to poppy field, zinnia field, aster field, and daffodil field. The aster field is also connected to the poppy field, zinnia field, lavender field, and sunflower field. From the lily field what is the shortest path to the chrysanthemum field? Starting from lily, please list the flower names in order, including lily, separated by commas.

To find the shortest path from the lily field to the chrysanthemum field, we can use Dijkstra's algorithm. 

1. Start at the lily field.
2. Check the neighboring fields of the lily field: rose field, peony field, hydrangea field, and orchid field.
3. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the rose field is the closest.
4. Move to the rose field.
5. Check the neighboring fields of the rose field: sunflower field, tulip field, daisy field, and lily field.
6. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the daisy field is the closest.
7. Move to the daisy field.
8. Check the neighboring fields of the daisy field: rose field, sunflower field, tulip field, and zinnia field.
9. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the zinnia field is the closest.
10. Move to the zinnia field.
11. Check the neighboring fields of the zinnia field: daisy field, poppy field, lavender field, and aster field.
12. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the aster field is the closest.
13. Move to the aster field.
14. Check the neighboring fields of the aster field: poppy field, zinnia field, lavender field, and sunflower field.
15. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the sunflower field is the closest.
16. Move to the sunflower field.
17. Check the neighboring fields of the sunflower field: rose field, tulip field, daisy field, and aster field.
18. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the tulip field is the closest.
19. Move to the tulip field.
20. Check the neighboring fields of the tulip field: rose field, sunflower field, daisy field, and orchid field.
21. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the orchid field is the closest.
22. Move to the orchid field.
23. Check the neighboring fields of the orchid field: hydrangea field, lily field, daffodil field, and tulip field.
24. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the hydrangea field is the closest.
25. Move to the hydrangea field.
26. Check the neighboring fields of the hydrangea field: orchid field, lily field, peony field, and marigold field.
27. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the peony field is the closest.
28. Move to the peony field.
29. Check the neighboring fields of the peony field: orchid field, hydrangea field, lily field, and chrysanthemum field.
30. Among these neighboring fields, choose the one with the shortest distance. In this case, the chrysanthemum field is the closest.

Answer: Lily, Rose, Daisy, Zinnia, Aster, Sunflower, Tulip, Orchid, Hydrangea, Peony, Chrysanthemum
